The paper deals with information theory and coding, specifically lossy binary source coding with side information. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the Wyner-Ziv problem, which is a well-known problem in multimedia coding, indicating that the paper could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also deals with side information, which is a common topic in the cs.SI (Signal Processing) sub-category. The analysis of the binary asymmetric channel could also be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents an evaluation of the rate loss between two coding schemes, which could be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
